{"key":"processedPost-10520038","value":{"id":10520038,"first":10518852,"last":10520038,"when":1245211741,"utime":"06/17/09 07:09 AM","content":"Don't make the mistake of thinking humidity is more important than fresh air.&nbsp; Fresh air is the number one pinning trigger. You'll just have to experiment and tweak it until things are right.&nbsp; Get a good analog hygrometer and calibrate it via the damp towel method.<br /><br />Most coolmists blow straight up.&nbsp; If yours does, set it <i>beside</i> the shelves so it can blow all the way to the ceiling.&nbsp; This gives the mist time to be absorbed into the air.&nbsp; If the mist blows against shelves or trays, it will condense and rain back down, making a mess.<br />RR","title":"Re: Humidifier inside greenhouse the nitty gritty","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}